## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project demonstrates the **core text preprocessing techniques** used in NLP pipelines.  
It focuses on transforming unstructured text into clean, meaningful, and machine-readable numerical representations.

The goal of this project is **learning and clarity**, not complexity â€” understanding *why preprocessing matters* before moving to advanced NLP models.

---

## ğŸš€ Features Implemented

- ğŸ”¹ **Tokenization**
  - Sentence tokenization
  - Word tokenization

- ğŸ”¹ **Stop Words Removal**
  - Removing common words that add little semantic value

- ğŸ”¹ **Stemming**
  - Reducing words to their root form using Porter Stemmer

- ğŸ”¹ **Lemmatization**
  - Converting words into meaningful base forms using WordNet

- ğŸ”¹ **Bag of Words (BoW)**
  - Text vectorization using CountVectorizer

- ğŸ”¹ **TF-IDF**
  - Transforming text into numerical features based on term importance

